Description: Wall fragment of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery closed vessel (dinos or krater); interior reserved, wheelmarks; exterior: yellow-cream slip, and glaze partly fired reddish-brown: part of a goat grazing to left, with the tail of another on the left; traces of added red paint on neck of goat; filling ornament: rosette.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Ashmolean Museum, Oxford. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.
Published (as an oinochoe) in CVA Oxford 2, II D, p. 78, no. 4, pl. IV.
Bibliographic references: CVA Oxford II / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum Great Britain 9 Oxford fasicule 2 (II D, pl. IV, 4)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.423)
Previous owner: Currently owned by: Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford
